 Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Julia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Feminine form of the old Roman family name   Julius .  A woman called Julia is mentioned in Paul's Epistle to the Romans (Romans 16:15), and the name was borne by numerous early saints. Its frequency increased with the vogue for classical names in the 18th century, and it continues to enjoy considerable popularity, although the recent introduction of   Julie   to the English-speaking world has reduced this somewhat. Well-known bearers include the British actress  Julia Foster  (  b. 1941 ) and American actress  Julia Roberts  (  b. 1967  as  Julie Fiona Roberts )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Julia Ellinbrygge was born in 1345, in Banstead, Surrey, England, United Kingdom. She married Ralph Lambert about 1377, in Banstead, Surrey, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died after 1389, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1345–Aft 1389":"1345–pärast 1389","1340–1420":"1340–1420","1380–1432":"1380–1432","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1385–1420":"1385–1420","1389–Female":"1389–Surnud","1345–1389":"1345–1389","Aft 1389":"pärast 1389","1345":"1345","1389":"1389","1432":"1432","1420":"1420","ABT 1377":"umbes 1377","1385":"1385","1340":"1340","Abt 1389":"umbes 1389","Abt 1380":"umbes 1380","1380":"1380","Banstead, Reigate and Banstead, Surrey, England, United Kingdom":"Banstead, Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of, Banstead, Surrey, England":"Banstead, Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Winterwell, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Woodmansterne, Surrey, England":"Woodmansterne, Surrey, England","Banstead, Surrey, England":"Banstead, Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1345–Aft 1389":"1345–1389 jälkeen","1340–1420":"1340–1420","1380–1432"